.TH _printf 3 2026-03-19 "_printf Holberton School Project"
.SH NAME
_printf, print_char, print_str, print_format - custom printf implementation
.SH FUNCTIONS USED
.TP
.B _printf
Main function. Parses the format string and calls print_format for each specifier.
.TP
.B print_char
Prints a single character to stdout.
.TP
.B print_str
Prints a string to stdout.
.TP
.B print_format
Dispatches to the correct print function based on the conversion specifier.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B #include "main.h"
.PP
.BI "int _printf(const char " format ", ...);"
.PP
.BI "int print_char(int " c ");"
.PP
.BI "int print_str(char" str ");"
.PP
.BI "int print_format(char " specifier ", va_list " ap ");"
.SH DESCRIPTION
.TP
.B _printf
Produces output to stdout according to a format string. Walks through
the format string character by character. Ordinary characters are printed
as-is. When a % is found, the next character is passed to print_format
to handle the conversion specifier.
.TP
.B print_char
Takes an integer c and writes it to stdout as a single character.
Returns 1 on success.
.TP
.B print_str
Takes a string pointer and prints each character to stdout until the
null terminator is reached. If the pointer is NULL, prints (null) instead.
Returns the number of characters printed.
.TP
.B print_format
Takes a specifier character and a va_list. Uses a switch statement to
call the correct print function. Handles %c, %s, %d, %i, and %%.
Unknown specifiers print the % followed by the unknown character.
.SH OUTPUT
.TP
.B %c
Prints a single character.
.TP
.B %s
Prints a string. Prints (null) if pointer is NULL.
.TP
.B %d, %i
Prints a signed decimal integer. Handles negative numbers and INT_MIN.
.TP
.B %%
Prints a literal percent sign.
.SH RETURN VALUE
.B _printf
returns the number of characters printed, excluding the null terminator.
Returns -1 if format is NULL or format ends with an unhandled %.
